Introduction

BXB is a six-member boy group under Wolfburn. They made their debut on January 30, 2023, with their first single album titled "Intro: Flight and a New Beginning".

The group's name BXB is an acronym for "Boy By Brush", which represents their mission to paint vivid pictures of youth through music of various genres. Before debut, they went by APR PROJECT.

On April 29, 2023, Wolfburn announced that June would be going on hiatus due to health issues.

The fandom name "GREAM" refers to BXB, who draws the youth of 'Boy By Brush', and the fans who draw 'DREAM', meaning that all the dreams and stories of youth are completed in one picture.

On February 18, 2025, BXB revealed their new member, Yuki, in an official trailer for their first Japanese single, "Chapter 3: Journey."
